Asiana Airlines flight OZ162 made a tailstrike and skidded off the runway at Hiroshima Airport in Japan . 
  There were 74 passengers and seven crew members on board the Airbus A320 . 
  The plane spun 180 degrees after impact and was left facing the wrong way on the runway . 
  Twenty people are believed to have been injured in the crash . 
  The airport has been closed and emergency services are at the scene . 
 